246
00:17:59.360 --> 00:18:01.044
So. why haven't you moved on. then?

247
00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:03.441
Because no one tried to
push an XO badge on me.

248
00:18:03.560 --> 00:18:04.800
I like things the way they are.

249
00:18:04.840 --> 00:18:06.171
Evolve or die.

250
00:18:06.240 --> 00:18:08.083
Then at least I'll die grinning.

251
00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:10.049
Don't be stupid. One of these days.

252
00:18:10.120 --> 00:18:12.851
Earth and Mars are gonna bury the
hatchet and hammer out a treaty.

253
00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:15.002
Yeah. and now you're dreamin'. Cap.

254
00:18:15.080 --> 00:18:16.889
I'm a man of great vision. You'll see.

255
00:18:16.960 --> 00:18:19.016
Means we'll finally get out
of the ice-hauling business

256
00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:21.008
and into the Earth-Mars business.

257
00:18:21.120 --> 00:18:23.202
Less risk. way better reward.

258
00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:25.929
Maybe a chance to see Earth again.

259
00:18:26.040 --> 00:18:28.088
What makes you think I
wanna see Earth again?

260
00:18:28.240 --> 00:18:30.242
You a "wanted man" back in Montana?

261
00:18:30.320 --> 00:18:31.401
Maybe I am.

262
00:18:31.480 --> 00:18:33.369
Someday you'll tell me that story.

263
00:18:33.560 --> 00:18:36.450
Right after you tell me
the story about those.

264
00:18:37.280 --> 00:18:40.284
Well. those are. uh. mine.

265
00:18:40.960 --> 00:18:42.769
It's just... There's...

266
00:18:43.840 --> 00:18:45.080
I don't care about your past.

267
00:18:45.160 --> 00:18:46.936
Everybody on the <i>Cant</i> is
hiding from something.

268
00:18:46.960 --> 00:18:48.644
Yeah. I appreciate the offer. Cap.

269
00:18:48.720 --> 00:18:52.281
<i>Hey. boss. we need you out here.
You gotta see this.</i>

270
00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:54.684
Hang on to this for a couple of days.

271
00:18:54.760 --> 00:18:56.683
It might feel good in the pocket.

272
00:19:03.520 --> 00:19:04.806
Picked up a Mayday.

273
00:19:05.480 --> 00:19:08.324
Looks like a light freighter.
Calls itself the <i>Scopuli.</i>

274
00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:09.640
Anyone else in the vicinity?

275
00:19:09.720 --> 00:19:12.883
No siree. Bob. we are the only
ship in three million clicks.

276
00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:14.286
- Of course we are.
- Got it.

277
00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:17.803
Next to a charted. non-Belt asteroid.

278
00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:20.527
What the hell were they
doing way out there?

279
00:19:20.600 --> 00:19:22.329
We're obligated to check it out.

280
00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:24.926
I'm well aware of the statute. Ms. Nygaard.

281
00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:32.721
It's pirate bait.

282
00:19:32.800 --> 00:19:35.007
That far outside the shipping lanes?

283
00:19:35.080 --> 00:19:38.448
It's not far out of our way. Captain.
Two days at most.

284
00:19:41.480 --> 00:19:43.608
A delay means we lose our berth at Ceres.

285
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.650
Kiss our on-time bonus goodbye.

286
00:19:49.360 --> 00:19:52.125
I say we move on and let the
good God Darwin sort it out.

287
00:19:55.320 --> 00:19:57.209
What goes around comes around.

288
00:19:57.280 --> 00:19:59.965
One of these days. it's gonna
be us stranded out there.

289
00:20:03.800 --> 00:20:05.928
Captain gave an order. people.

290
00:20:06.600 --> 00:20:09.126
Purge the logs. We never
received that signal.

291
00:20:10.840 --> 00:20:13.002
Set the watch and proceed.

292
00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:20.043
See. you're a natural.

293
00:20:20.600 --> 00:20:22.967
That was some real XO shit in there.

294
00:20:23.040 --> 00:20:26.806
No. That was me wanting to
get to Ceres worse than you.

295
00:20:42.619 --> 00:20:45.270
<i>Thanks for backing me up
on that distress call.</i>

296
00:20:45.579 --> 00:20:48.059
McDowell's got a nose for trouble.

297
00:20:48.139 --> 00:20:50.460
He's been doing this a
while longer than we have.

298
00:20:50.539 --> 00:20:53.065
I guess you really are sucking
up for that XO badge.

299
00:20:53.459 --> 00:20:54.949
Turned him down flat.

300
00:20:55.019 --> 00:20:56.430
You kidding me?

301
00:20:57.019 --> 00:20:58.987
You'd be on the short path to Captain.

302
00:20:59.099 --> 00:21:00.339
Exactly.

303
00:21:01.259 --> 00:21:05.230
Besides. if I took it. we'd
have to stop seeing each other.

304
00:21:06.459 --> 00:21:08.223
Well. You know.

305
00:21:08.299 --> 00:21:11.462
There's that saying about all good things.

306
00:21:14.979 --> 00:21:18.540
I told you. A couple more
rotations and I'd be moving on.

307
00:21:19.139 --> 00:21:21.221
A couple is.

308
00:21:21.299 --> 00:21:24.542
you know. two at least. I assumed.

309
00:21:24.619 --> 00:21:25.780
Hey.

310
00:21:26.579 --> 00:21:28.502
There's right now and there's later.

311
00:21:28.939 --> 00:21:30.589
Why worry about later. right?

312
00:21:30.659 --> 00:21:31.820
Right.

313
00:21:33.379 --> 00:21:35.222
Come on. Jim. Lie down.

314
00:21:36.699 --> 00:21:40.385
I promise I won't lay a finger on you.

315
00:21:51.899 --> 00:21:53.788
I can't sleep. I'll take over.

316
00:21:55.219 --> 00:21:56.459
I'll buy you a bottle on Ceres.

317
00:21:56.499 --> 00:21:59.343
I'll settle for a good cup of coffee.

318
00:23:08.779 --> 00:23:10.588
<i>Please help me.</i>

319
00:23:11.419 --> 00:23:13.660
<i>Is anybody there? Please.</i>

320
00:23:27.219 --> 00:23:28.869
<i>Please help me.</i>

321
00:23:53.059 --> 00:23:54.709
Hey!

322
00:23:56.299 --> 00:23:57.949
How many times have I told you?

323
00:23:58.019 --> 00:23:59.942
This calls for tickling!

324
00:24:00.299 --> 00:24:01.903
No!

325
00:24:01.979 --> 00:24:04.949
No. please. no!

326
00:24:06.619 --> 00:24:08.462
He'll wet himself if you're not careful.

327
00:24:08.579 --> 00:24:11.389
That's the advantage of
being a grandparent.

328
00:24:11.499 --> 00:24:13.900
I get to hand him off to his mother.

329
00:24:21.979 --> 00:24:24.710
<i>Amma.</i> do you have to go?

330
00:24:25.059 --> 00:24:27.266
Yes. I do. I'm sorry.

331
00:24:27.339 --> 00:24:29.262
There's someone I need to talk to.

332
00:24:29.339 --> 00:24:30.829
Are people fighting again?

333
00:24:30.899 --> 00:24:31.900
Not yet.

334
00:24:33.859 --> 00:24:37.147
<i>That's why we need to
talk. and tell the truth.</i>

335
00:24:40.059 --> 00:24:42.346
<i>When people don't tell the truth.</i>

336
00:24:42.419 --> 00:24:44.262
<i>it always ends badly.</i>

337
00:25:01.219 --> 00:25:03.620
You've been linked to a
radical faction of the OPA.

338
00:25:04.219 --> 00:25:05.869
Were you just a courier?

339
00:25:08.619 --> 00:25:10.621
How long has he been out of the tank?

340
00:25:10.699 --> 00:25:11.746
Ten hours.

341
00:25:18.379 --> 00:25:21.588
I'm sorry the gravity
of a real planet hurts.

342
00:25:21.899 --> 00:25:23.503
But it's appropriate.

343
00:25:24.179 --> 00:25:25.544
You wish to hurt Earth.

344
00:25:26.379 --> 00:25:30.668
The Earth that is now crushing
your weak Belter lungs.

345
00:25:30.739 --> 00:25:33.219
and your fragile Belter bones.

346
00:25:34.579 --> 00:25:37.503
All you have to do to make it stop is talk.

347
00:25:39.219 --> 00:25:41.142
You're an OPA terrorist.

348
00:25:41.219 --> 00:25:44.063
You were carrying contraband
stealth technology.

349
00:25:44.739 --> 00:25:46.423
What was it for?

350
00:25:50.019 --> 00:25:53.865
A whisper will do. if
that's all you can manage.

351
00:25:55.579 --> 00:25:57.104
Hey.

352
00:26:02.099 --> 00:26:04.067
Give him another 10 hours.

353
00:26:05.579 --> 00:26:07.422
If he survives. call me.

354
00:26:18.499 --> 00:26:21.309
<i>Now arriving. Medina Exchange District.</i>

355
00:26:25.939 --> 00:26:28.510
- Everybody calm down. all right!
- Back away.

356
00:26:28.579 --> 00:26:29.785
Back up. people!

357
00:26:40.579 --> 00:26:43.628
Hey! Back up. buddy. I'm talking to you!

358
00:26:44.299 --> 00:26:45.299
What's up. doll?

359
00:26:45.339 --> 00:26:46.829
Cheap-ass air filters crapped out.

360
00:26:46.899 --> 00:26:48.742
Second time this month.

361
00:26:50.659 --> 00:26:53.105
I guess this guy pays well
to be taken care of. huh?

362
00:26:54.619 --> 00:26:57.623
Yeah. he pays our bosses
pretty well. too. pal.

363
00:26:57.699 --> 00:27:00.145
Look. don't try to save the whole
station on your first day.

364
00:27:01.019 --> 00:27:02.305
Pace yourself.

365
00:27:05.859 --> 00:27:07.145
Any rain yet?

366
00:27:10.339 --> 00:27:12.706
That distress call we never received.

367
00:27:13.339 --> 00:27:14.989
it was logged with HQ.

368
00:27:15.699 --> 00:27:19.101
By some anonymous. piece-o'-shit
do-gooder aboard this ship.

369
00:27:19.179 --> 00:27:20.515
Well. at least somebody has a soul.

370
00:27:20.539 --> 00:27:21.745
I swear. I find the rat...

371
00:27:21.819 --> 00:27:23.755
Quit lookin' at me. Byers.
or I'll put your lights out.

372
00:27:23.779 --> 00:27:24.940
Any ol' time. girl.

373
00:27:25.019 --> 00:27:28.785
Now. we're forced to divert.
or the firm's legally on the hook.

374
00:27:28.859 --> 00:27:29.860
Holden.

375
00:27:30.499 --> 00:27:32.740
You'll head up this rescue. or salvage.

376
00:27:32.859 --> 00:27:34.463
whatever we're calling it.

377
00:27:35.339 --> 00:27:36.864
Put a shuttle team together.

378
00:27:40.459 --> 00:27:41.824
Is there a problem. XO?

379
00:27:42.059 --> 00:27:44.744
Acting XO. sir.

380
00:27:49.939 --> 00:27:51.748
I ain't goin'. No way. no how.

381
00:27:51.819 --> 00:27:53.264
Well. you ain't invited.

382
00:27:53.859 --> 00:27:55.907
Alex. ping the beacon that we're on our way

383
00:27:55.979 --> 00:27:57.947
and let Ceres know that
we're gonna be late.

384
00:27:58.059 --> 00:27:59.299
Ms. Nygaard?

385
00:27:59.379 --> 00:28:00.983
If we flip right now and burn like hell.

386
00:28:01.059 --> 00:28:02.823
I can get us within 50.000 clicks.

387
00:28:02.939 --> 00:28:05.180
Oh. great. Then we'll all be
puking in our crash-couches

388
00:28:05.259 --> 00:28:07.421
while the cargo busts loose
and scuttles the ship.

389
00:28:07.499 --> 00:28:08.989
Make sure that ice stays put.

390
00:28:09.539 --> 00:28:12.463
Naomi. How's the <i>Knight</i> looking?

391
00:28:12.539 --> 00:28:14.541
She's one leaky lifeboat.

392
00:28:14.659 --> 00:28:17.265
But she should be able to
manage 50.000 clicks of vacuum.

393
00:28:17.339 --> 00:28:19.103
All right. then you're on board.

394
00:28:24.419 --> 00:28:25.909
This is Holden.

395
00:28:25.979 --> 00:28:30.940
We've logged a distress
call near CA-2216862.

396
00:28:31.019 --> 00:28:33.499
<i>We're obliged to change
our course and respond.</i>

397
00:28:33.579 --> 00:28:36.310
<i>Make sure your acceleration
drug dispensers are full.</i>

398
00:28:36.379 --> 00:28:39.701
<i>This will be a high-G maneuver.
Prepare for flip and burn.</i>

399
00:28:55.539 --> 00:28:56.779
Here comes the juice.

400
00:30:28.742 --> 00:30:32.383
I can't figure out why Cap would put you
in charge of this little excursion.

401
00:30:32.662 --> 00:30:34.232
Well. he still thinks he's grooming me

402
00:30:34.302 --> 00:30:35.872
for bigger things.

403
00:30:35.942 --> 00:30:37.228
Then he's wasting his time.

404
00:30:38.102 --> 00:30:40.070
That's what I keep telling him.

405
00:30:44.142 --> 00:30:46.304
If your girlfriend logged
that distress call.

406
00:30:47.502 --> 00:30:50.108
she's gonna be living it
down for a long time.

407
00:30:56.662 --> 00:30:57.948
I did it.

408
00:31:04.022 --> 00:31:05.672
I just couldn't shake it.

409
00:31:08.342 --> 00:31:10.868
I'd keep that to myself if I were you.

410
00:31:17.062 --> 00:31:19.383
What's the good word. y'all?

411
00:31:20.182 --> 00:31:21.343
All right.

412
00:31:21.862 --> 00:31:24.183
How's my sweet old rust bucket today?

413
00:31:24.862 --> 00:31:27.263
Well. I guess we'll find out. won't we?

414
00:31:27.342 --> 00:31:28.753
I guess so.

415
00:31:30.782 --> 00:31:32.022
Okay.

416
00:31:36.062 --> 00:31:38.269
So just for the record. guys.

417
00:31:38.342 --> 00:31:39.832
I don't wanna be here right now.

418
00:31:39.902 --> 00:31:42.746
Me neither. But here we are.

419
00:31:42.822 --> 00:31:44.711
One big. happy unit.

420
00:31:45.062 --> 00:31:46.791
Knight. <i>your flight plan is set.</i>

421
00:31:46.862 --> 00:31:49.513
<i>It'll be a two-hour trip to
the tango. flying tea-kettle.</i>

422
00:31:49.582 --> 00:31:50.913
<i>Thank you.</i> Canterbury.

423
00:31:51.342 --> 00:31:53.993
<i>Welcome.</i> Knight. <i>Godspeed.</i>

424
00:31:54.062 --> 00:31:57.145
If you see anything that seems off. you
pack up the toys and come on home.

425
00:31:57.222 --> 00:31:58.986
No heroes. Captain.

426
00:31:59.062 --> 00:32:01.508
Clear to leave the barn. Good luck.

427
00:32:31.102 --> 00:32:32.103
Really?

428
00:32:35.422 --> 00:32:36.423
She's off the clock.

429
00:32:37.662 --> 00:32:39.585
Then she can tell me that.

430
00:32:52.062 --> 00:32:53.268
I'd keep an eye on that guy.

431
00:32:53.582 --> 00:32:57.189
I hear he collects moon
rocks in his spare time.

432
00:32:57.782 --> 00:32:59.546
You wanna know what else he's into?

433
00:32:59.622 --> 00:33:03.547
Hey. hey. now. I'm just
lookin' out for you.

434
00:33:05.422 --> 00:33:06.833
I need a woman's intuition.

435
00:33:08.982 --> 00:33:09.982
Who is she?

436
00:33:10.022 --> 00:33:12.946
Oh. she's just a missing-persons case

437
00:33:13.022 --> 00:33:15.502
I'm not "permitted to discuss." you know.

438
00:33:16.982 --> 00:33:18.984
Juliette Andromeda Mao.

439
00:33:19.542 --> 00:33:21.988
She's the richest
bachelorette in the system.

440
00:33:23.142 --> 00:33:25.190
Now what would a rich girl do

441
00:33:25.982 --> 00:33:28.906
to really piss Daddy off on Ceres?

442
00:33:28.982 --> 00:33:30.313
Are you asking what I did?

443
00:33:32.062 --> 00:33:34.224
Bang every space bucker I could find.

444
00:33:35.582 --> 00:33:37.186
That's not helpful.

445
00:33:37.302 --> 00:33:39.430
Oh. I'm sorry. Miller. Did
you come here for my help?

446
00:33:40.022 --> 00:33:41.672
Come on.

447
00:33:42.302 --> 00:33:46.102
Admit it. You miss me. You
miss these little chats.

448
00:33:46.982 --> 00:33:48.666
Good night. Miller.

449
00:33:56.462 --> 00:33:59.386
Eat something. for God's sake.
You look like hell.

450
00:34:18.782 --> 00:34:20.705
<i>Config matches the registry information.</i>

451
00:34:22.702 --> 00:34:24.227
It's definitely the <i>Scopuli.</i>

452
00:34:24.782 --> 00:34:27.865
No IR or electro-mag other
than the distress beacon.

453
00:34:28.542 --> 00:34:29.942
Looks like the reactor's shut down.

454
00:34:29.982 --> 00:34:31.472
but no radiation leakage.

455
00:34:33.382 --> 00:34:36.386
What about that thing that looks
like a big hole in the side?

456
00:34:37.662 --> 00:34:40.632
Uh. LADAR says it's a big hole in the side.

457
00:34:43.502 --> 00:34:47.552
Well. the big array on the <i>Cant's</i>
reading no one within a million clicks.

458
00:34:47.822 --> 00:34:49.631
Looks like we're the only game in town.

459
00:34:49.702 --> 00:34:52.069
Well. we came. we looked. we. uh. left.

460
00:34:52.982 --> 00:34:55.428
No one's gonna know if we
set foot on that thing.

461
00:34:58.582 --> 00:34:59.708
Take us in.

462
00:35:00.542 --> 00:35:03.625
And. Alex. if something
nasty's hiding in that ship.

463
00:35:03.702 --> 00:35:06.069
we bolt like hell and melt
anything behind us into slag.

464
00:35:06.182 --> 00:35:07.343
Good plan. Hoss.

465
00:35:07.422 --> 00:35:09.743
All right. I'll go in and poke around.

466
00:35:12.062 --> 00:35:13.427
I'll go with him.

467
00:35:30.302 --> 00:35:31.713
Good times.

468
00:36:06.731 --> 00:36:08.813
How do you think that happened?

469
00:36:10.091 --> 00:36:13.334
It wasn't a torpedo. A
breaching charge did that.

470
00:36:18.971 --> 00:36:20.052
Amos.

471
00:36:21.451 --> 00:36:22.976
Keep that gun out.

472
00:36:25.331 --> 00:36:28.813
Engineering first. I wanna know
why that reactor's offline.

473
00:36:44.411 --> 00:36:46.937
Reactor wasn't killed by the blast.

474
00:36:48.251 --> 00:36:50.857
Someone went through the
shutdown procedures.

475
00:36:52.491 --> 00:36:54.892
So. if everyone's dead. who turned it off?

476
00:36:55.851 --> 00:36:57.694
Well. it wasn't pirates.

477
00:36:58.931 --> 00:37:00.535
They wouldn't have left all that behind.

478
00:37:01.371 --> 00:37:03.658
And they left all the pressure doors open.

479
00:37:07.091 --> 00:37:08.900
So no one could hide.

480
00:37:13.611 --> 00:37:14.817
Six o'clock!

481
00:37:18.371 --> 00:37:21.136
Naomi. Shed. we need more eyes in here.

482
00:37:23.411 --> 00:37:25.015
All right. Meet us on the bridge.

483
00:37:42.051 --> 00:37:43.541
Hey. guys?

484
00:37:45.051 --> 00:37:47.019
Where are all the bodies at?

485
00:37:47.451 --> 00:37:51.661
Amos. cut out the data core.
We'll take it with us.

486
00:37:52.611 --> 00:37:53.897
Roger that.

487
00:37:58.091 --> 00:38:00.219
These panels are all dead.

488
00:38:00.811 --> 00:38:03.815
How are they sending a distress
beacon with dead comms?

489
00:38:22.651 --> 00:38:23.777
Does that look like a...

490
00:38:24.291 --> 00:38:25.417
Well. maybe not...

491
00:38:26.131 --> 00:38:28.418
If it was a bomb. we'd be toast.

492
00:38:30.371 --> 00:38:32.055
It's a transmitter.

493
00:38:36.251 --> 00:38:38.618
This must be the beacon that called us.

494
00:38:38.731 --> 00:38:40.620
Somebody planted it.

495
00:38:40.731 --> 00:38:42.096
Pirate bait.

496
00:38:43.331 --> 00:38:44.537
McDowell was right.

497
00:38:45.251 --> 00:38:49.097
<i>Hoss. forwarding you an A-1
tight-beam from the</i> Canterbury.

498
00:38:49.971 --> 00:38:53.339
Holden. a ship just appeared
near your location.

499
00:38:53.411 --> 00:38:56.654
<i>How is that possible? You
cleared us out to a million clicks.</i>

500
00:38:57.331 --> 00:38:59.413
It didn't show up on any of our scopes.

501
00:38:59.491 --> 00:39:03.177
We're setting you a rendezvous point.
Get the hell back here.

502
00:39:14.091 --> 00:39:15.377
Alex! Disengage!

503
00:39:15.451 --> 00:39:16.498
My pleasure.

504
00:39:19.171 --> 00:39:20.377
Disengaging!

505
00:39:30.891 --> 00:39:32.131
Where did that thing come from?

506
00:39:32.171 --> 00:39:34.412
Damned if I know! Just
suddenly. it was there.

507
00:39:34.771 --> 00:39:36.341
Stealth tech. Has to be.

508
00:39:36.451 --> 00:39:38.215
Who the hell has stealth like that?

509
00:39:39.891 --> 00:39:40.892
Mars.

510
00:39:56.824 --> 00:39:58.747
That's more thinner to the mix. all right?

511
00:39:58.824 --> 00:39:59.950
All right.

512
00:40:00.064 --> 00:40:02.431
Hey. hey. you see that other one?

513
00:40:02.504 --> 00:40:04.472
What was that? You got
that other one with you?

514
00:40:06.184 --> 00:40:09.074
That's a cute kid. How old?

515
00:40:09.424 --> 00:40:10.664
Two and a half.

516
00:40:11.664 --> 00:40:12.711
Hi.

517
00:40:14.024 --> 00:40:15.913
How about you? Any kids?

518
00:40:17.504 --> 00:40:20.474
Yeah. no. I missed that boat.

519
00:40:44.864 --> 00:40:46.275
There you go. pal.

520
00:40:49.584 --> 00:40:51.586
My turn.

521
00:40:52.424 --> 00:40:54.392
My turn.

522
00:40:54.744 --> 00:40:56.792
Me turn. me turn!

523
00:41:06.984 --> 00:41:09.351
We had an understanding. Detective!
An arrangement!

524
00:41:09.424 --> 00:41:11.552
You can't just... It was a mistake!

525
00:41:22.264 --> 00:41:25.473
You made your point. I'm a changed man!

526
00:41:25.544 --> 00:41:27.512
Thank you for opening my eyes!

527
00:41:31.984 --> 00:41:33.509
Twice the money!

528
00:41:35.264 --> 00:41:36.993
I'll pay you double!

529
00:41:44.784 --> 00:41:47.628
Air is good. don't you think?

530
00:41:50.024 --> 00:41:51.435
Air is nice.

531
00:41:53.944 --> 00:41:55.946
Keep those filters clean. asshole.

532
00:42:00.024 --> 00:42:01.240
<i>Knight.</i> we have your rendezvous.

533
00:42:01.264 --> 00:42:02.265
Negative. Unable.

534
00:42:02.344 --> 00:42:03.550
Advise.

535
00:42:03.624 --> 00:42:05.513
Bogey is 12.000 clicks and closing.

536
00:42:05.584 --> 00:42:06.585
<i>Holden. advise!</i>

537
00:42:10.904 --> 00:42:11.985
Torpedo launch!

538
00:42:12.064 --> 00:42:14.240
We're gonna take 'em for a ride.
Alex. go around the asteroid.

539
00:42:14.264 --> 00:42:17.234
Run 'em! Now! Lead the
torpedoes into the rock.

540
00:42:17.304 --> 00:42:19.511
<i>What is your situation? Please advise!</i>

541
00:42:22.984 --> 00:42:24.224
Six thousand clicks.

542
00:42:25.224 --> 00:42:27.905
Five... Four...

543
00:42:28.824 --> 00:42:30.314
Three...

544
00:42:40.704 --> 00:42:42.035
Those weren't meant for us.

545
00:42:44.864 --> 00:42:47.185
<i>Canterbury.</i> burn like hell.
you've got incoming!

546
00:42:50.504 --> 00:42:52.984
Right 30. G-burn. Do it! Now!

547
00:42:53.464 --> 00:42:55.432
Range? Two-four. Closing.

548
00:42:55.504 --> 00:42:56.710
Standby cargo door.

549
00:42:56.824 --> 00:42:58.269
Captain. eject the ice as a shield.

550
00:42:58.344 --> 00:42:59.834
We're on it! Stay off this channel.

551
00:42:59.904 --> 00:43:01.190
Ade?

552
00:43:01.264 --> 00:43:03.187
<i>Ade. did Mac eject the ice?</i>

553
00:43:03.464 --> 00:43:04.670
Did he eject the ice?

554
00:43:05.704 --> 00:43:08.355
You take a hit. you stay calm.
They just want the cargo.

555
00:43:08.424 --> 00:43:10.640
We'll SOS. start negotiations
for prisoner release. okay?

556
00:43:10.664 --> 00:43:11.790
Just... <i>Jim.</i>

557
00:43:11.864 --> 00:43:13.304
<i>There's something you should know...</i>

558
00:43:46.184 --> 00:43:47.424
She's gone.

559
00:43:59.184 --> 00:44:00.595
They nuked her.

560
00:44:03.344 --> 00:44:04.584
She's gone.

561
00:44:19.668 --> 00:44:23.668
Synced:
<i><font color=#800080>teidy</font></i>

562
00:44:24.305 --> 00:45:24.505
